subSubSection.paragraph:
Cell V rectangular in optical section, as long as cell IV. Septum IV–V vertical, connected with septum III–IV. Outer appendage consisting of 2–3 rather straight, apparently rigid, elongate branches arising above the suprabasal cell which bears a dorsal additional branch, often reduced to a rimmed darkened expansion (
Fig. 29A
, arrow). Inner appendage consisting of a basal cell which is half as long as the outer basal cell, giving rise to 1–2 simple or once ramified branches bearing 1–2 apical antheridia each. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1896
; 
Sugiyama 1973
; 
Majewski 1994b
; 
Santamaria 1998
]

